I wonder if we should add config override like: https://github.com/HotelsDotCom/circus-train/blob/c5b428173bafb1339713aee43958dd27904dc0c4/circus-train-core/src/main/java/com/hotels/bdp/circustrain/core/DefaultCopierFactoryManager.java#L64
@massdosage  what do you think?
My concern is that someone overrides a s3s3Copier factory but gets a S3s3DataManipulationClient which then doesn't instantiate the AWS client correctly cause of the differences between a s3MapReduceOptions and S3S3Options.

